author: Geoff Butcher
comment: This is a useful app but you can't always rely on it to find the nearest business. I was 1/2 mile from a b&q but the nearest it found was over 7 miles away. After the new update wanted my identity I decided to uninstall it. To be honest a Google search will find as much or more info on local businesses as Yell does.

reply.author: Yell Limited
reply.content: Hi Geoff, thanks for your review. Sorry that the App isn’t living up to expectations, we’re always working hard to improve the quality of our data. Regarding the ‘identity’ permission, it’s only used to store your Yell Reviews account into your phone’s account section, nothing else. If you'd like to know more just get in touch app-preview@yell.com

author: Inka Pinka
comment: Useless since the upgrade... :( need the map to show local competition... No longer available since last upgrade. Will therefore no longer use :(

reply.author: Yell Limited
reply.content: Hi Inka! Thanks for your review and sorry we made the map harder to find. The good news is that it’s still there! When you’re on the results list, just tap the little map icon in the top right and you’ll see the map in all it’s glory! Hopefully I was able to help? If not, please do email me at apps@yell.com

author: Michelle Leanne Greyling
comment: Great

Essential app for getting a number for a business without the unnecessary 118 (con) service! Handy there's user reviews on a business too and that I can easily add a number from the app to my contact list. If only yellow pages would stop delivering their outdated (now there's the app) catalogue to my door! 5★

As another reviewer has remarked, this might be OK if you live in a big English city. But in S.Scotland it's a waste of time. Listed 4 cafes in an area I know has over 30 - none at all in a town that has half a dozen. 1 pub listed in a town with half a dozen. Waste of storage. Uninstalled.
